Jenni Evans, News24Cape Town Freeway (Twitter) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - The N2 between Spine and Baden Powell roads in Cape Town has been closed because of a massive veld fire that is being fanned by the wind, Western Cape traffic spokesperson Kenny Africa said on Sunday.''Visibility is very poor and there are huge flames because of strong winds,'' he said.The highway is closed in both directions.Nobody has been injured and there have been no accidents.Motorists should find alternative routes until the all clear is given, he said.Cape Town - N2 Highway (Update), #FIRE ROAD CLOSED at Khayelitsha, via @gthompbj pic.twitter.com/LXfSlIYs2x&mdash; Rob Byrne (@TrafficSA) January 3, 2016Cape Town - N2 Highway (Update), #FIRE ROAD CLOSED at Khayelitsha, via @gthompbj pic.twitter.com/LXfSlIYs2x#CPTTraffic - N2 closed before R300 due to veld fire. Inbound traffic is redirect onto R310. Use M40 for detour. pic.twitter.com/GYcXlrxFZM&mdash; Netstar Traffic (@netstartraffic) January 3, 2016#CPTTraffic - N2 closed before R300 due to veld fire. Inbound traffic is redirect onto R310. Use M40 for detour. pic.twitter.com/GYcXlrxFZM24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.